<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-10489] UserGroupInformation#getTokens and UserGroupInformation#addToken can lead to ConcurrentModificationException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10489</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently UserGroupInformation#getTokens and UserGroupInformation#addToken uses UGI&apos;s monitor to protect the iteration and modification of Credentials#tokenMap. Per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10475?focusedCommentId=13965851&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-13965851&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;discussion&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10475&quot; title=&quot;ConcurrentModificationException in AbstractDelegationTokenSelector.selectToken()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-10475&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-10475&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, this can still lead to ConcurrentModificationException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12707800">HADOOP-10489</key>
