                            <comment id="13998372" author="rkanter" created="Thu, 15 May 2014 01:57:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As suggested in the discussion in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10475&quot; title=&quot;ConcurrentModificationException in AbstractDelegationTokenSelector.selectToken()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-10475&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-10475&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I synchronized the methods on the &lt;tt&gt;subject&lt;/tt&gt; instead of the UGI.  I also added a test that runs a thread that repeatedly calls &lt;tt&gt;getTokens()&lt;/tt&gt; while the test calls &lt;tt&gt;addToken(...)&lt;/tt&gt; to cause the CME; it fails without the fix and passes with them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
